Market 

Analysis and Size





Text analytics are being deployed with data visualization tools among enterprises to understand numbers and make better decisions. In the past years, it has been highly useful to organizations for evaluating text in a wide range of languages, and acquiring a deeper understanding of customer opinions.

Global Text Analytics Market was valued at USD 6.45 billion in 2021 and is expected to reach USD 23.76 billion by 2029, registering a CAGR of 17.70% during the forecast period of 2022-2029. Retail and Ecommerce account for the largest industry vertical segment in the respective market owing to the high adoption among organizations to provide personalized schemes and discounts to their customers. In addition to the market insights such as market value, growth rate, market segments, geographical coverage, market players, and market scenario, the market report curated by the Data Bridge Market Research team also includes in-depth expert analysis, import/export analysis, pricing analysis, production consumption analysis, and pestle analysis.

Market Definition

Text analytics is defined as the automated process of translating vast amount of unstructured text, such as online reviews, call center agent notes, survey results, emails, and tweets, into quantitative data. This process delivers insights about trends. The technology mainly relies on natural language processing (NLP) algorithms and text mining to find meaning from written communication.

